{
  "texts": [
    "Table 2 shows the performance differences between our final strategy (the best RST variant) and other comparative models.",
    "Specifically, GPT-4 exhibits the poorest overall performance, attributable to a lack of parameter tuning.",
    "The performance of the models based on Vicuna as backbone is overall better than the models based on Longformer due to the larger number of parameters.",
    "Regarding parameter-efficient settings, vanilla LoRA's performance is marginally lower than FFT across most datasets, except eLife.",
    "However, LoRA achieves comparable results to FFT while only requiring adjustments of 0.25% of parameters for Longformer and 0.05% for Vicuna, highlighting LoRA's efficiency."
  ]
}